reviews.text: Went there after midnight on a Sunday. Was served by a a little rough lady server. Ordered a Grey goose martini with a lemon twist and it came out with a lemon slice inside the martini. And then there was water dripping on my head as there was condensation in the air conditioning above me . It was my first time here but will surely be my last time here too. The bar in Causeway Bay Crown Plaza is definitely much better and the staffs are much more professional and well trained too

Absolutely terrible service.
Between me and my friends, we flagged down waiters 4 TIMES and they would raise their hand to acknowledge that they will come later. Then they proceed to not come at all. One waiter we initially flagged down (who acknowledged us) then proceeded to stand at the back of the restaurant, staring at us as we tried to get the attention of a second waiter. 
I have never experienced such appalling service anywhere, even at low-end establishments like daipaidongs or chachaantengs and this is a hotel bar. 
It also took two bartenders, on a quiet night, 15 minutes to make a mojito. They also completely disregarded instructions about how to make a gin and tonic (gin separately please, with less ice). 

Very unprofessional and disappointing.

It’s my fiends birthday today and we came here for celebrations. The view of this restaurant is stunning and we were arranged with middle seats. It’s great ambience tho the menu is a bit pricey. If you book from the OpenRice App you can enjoy a 20% off and we found out the the HsBc card offer 25% off. We ordered the tomahawk which tastes the best. The semi buffet bar was fine with various kind of chases and salad to choose from with 5 to 6 dishes of desserts. If you pick the steak the buffet is at a cost of $150 hkd. Kinda good deal

This is a place where you couldn’t spend more even if you wanted to. 

They take more than 10 mins to attend to you / to even acknowledge your presence as the staff all walk right past you while you stand at the front counter on arrival. Meanwhile the queue formed behind us and everyone was wondering if this was the kind of place where they should just seat themselves. 

Subsequently, I asked for the wine menu 4 times in a span of 45 mins then gave up and left to walk back to the front counter to just close the tab and leave for the evening. 

This was on a Friday night. it appeared they only had 3 wait staff. I would be lying if I said the place was packed to brim. Note that this is notwithstanding that they impose a minimum spend requirement on Friday and Saturdays.
Great outdoors terrace and good drinks menu. Staff are friendly.

reviews.text:
昨晚去了黃金海岸酒店在比較下，發覺這間皇冠酒店除了政策上有問題外，就是負責房務的管理層是 (蠢同懶) 蠢到冇人有 黃金海岸酒店原來都是用兩張單人床拼埋做雙人床，但人家會用番張雙人床墊放番上面咁就瞓得舒服好多了，而不是懶同蠢到就咁張兩張單人床拼埋就當雙人床，真係笑死人，又要懶 但人又蠢真係冇藥醫 !!
原該酒店的政策如果經第三方預訂房間的話，你們就成為 次等住客，所有安排都只會給官網預訂的住客優先處理，點解比同一價錢卻得不到平等待遇，這種政策像是在侮辱緊使用旅行網站的顧客 及其為該酒店分銷服務的網站！(而我的要求只是想安排一張過的大床) 前台職員話冇房 跟著說你經第三方預訂......... 官網就 ..,,, 你下次 ...... 我再三請求結果都是一樣兩張單人床拼在一起的所謂大床房，睡也睡得不舒服，還有每次打開廁所門總是有點臭味，當晚亦領教過該集團的顧客關係部的員工，真只可說一句使人遺憾，什麼都不清楚 不知道，但我會尊重酒店的決定( 默認了嗎？) 而上海經客戶關係部留了聯絡電話給該酒店的前台經理至今超過一日仍未有任何來電！！

Nice hotel for functions (weddings, birthdays and family gatherings) with two huge function rooms. Chinese banquet was standard and tasty, very high ceilings made the room feel spacious and plenty of space for large bouncy castle and decorations. Complimentary valet parking was a bonus
今天六月廿四号下午约一時左右check out，身穿全白色的女接待員给了一張退回按金的纸我簽名，她核對了發覺簽名不同，我才發现是自己大意跟她说應該是我女兒簽的，換来一個亳無表情的反應及女兒補簽時那女接待員惡劣態度的對待，好像我們是在求她一樣，不明白五星级酒店內為何會有這樣的員工，希望有關公司培訓多一些尊業人才，令到住客有賓至如歸的感覺！

Good location, easy to get to. Food quality is super. Chef was able to prepare  food exactly as client's requirements. Good food. I ordered special asparagus dinner. The soup was hot and tasty. The beef was exactly medium rare as I requested.$688 with wine pairing before  service charge. Nice atmosphere with soft music and romantic lighting. But no discount even made booking through Open Rice. Cheating.

這間酒店的服務真的讓人很無語。我們使用Asia mile兌換了下午茶voucher，在電話booking時說明：「我們想book明天下午3：30、四位，是使用Asia mile tea set voucher。」
然後接線生竟然問：「sorry請問你是已經訂位了還是現在訂？」
我心想誰會已經訂了然後再打電話來訂？？？
然後我說是現在訂，3：30 四位。接線生說：「兩位是嗎？」是在做夢嗎？

經過無語的電話預訂後，今天到酒店用餐。
在reception被接待時侍應只確認了姓氏及電話就被帶入座了。我們以為他們在電腦系統已知道是使用Asia mile voucher。後來入座後同伴正在看餐牌，我把voucher拿出來再看看上面的說明，這時候服務生才走過來問我：「請問妳是要用voucher嗎？Voucher的話在我們餐牌只包含這一頁的全部餐點，另一頁是不包的。」
如果今天我到結帳前才把voucher拿出來那我們就不會知道只有包那份餐點而誤點了其他東西。正常來說不是應該從帶位時就向我們確認嗎？我不是從電話booking已清晰說明了用餐卷嗎？

餐點的味道見人見智，不多作評論。

到結帳時因為不知餐卷是否已包含服務費，所以叫了服務生。後來服務生把voucher拿來才向我們說明：「不好意思因為此餐卷上面寫明只包含星期一至五才能使用，今天是清明節所以需要補差額$44。」（今天是星期五，清明節）
我們問：「那麼為何昨天在電話booking及收voucher時你們並沒有向我說明？」
她回答：「因為Asia mile的餐卷有分兩種，昨天的同事可能也不太清楚，而我也是剛剛才看到上面的說明。」

雖然補的差額不多但如此粗心大意又無言的服務真的很不敢恭維。
